-- Cimpor Shares Rise as Much as 10% in Lisbon After Camargo Bid
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2012-04-02T07:12:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/cimpor-shares-rise-as-much-as-10-in-lisbon-after-camargo-bid.html
Cimpor-Cimentos de Portugal SGPS SA 
advanced as much as 10 percent in Lisbon trading after Camargo
Correa SA,  Brazil ’s No. 2 construction company, offered 2.48
billion euros ($3.31 billion) for the 67 percent it doesn’t
already own in  Portugal ’s biggest cement producer.  Cimpor  shares  climbed as much as 50 euro cents to 5.50
euros, the biggest gain since December 2010. The stock traded at
5.497 euros at 8:11 a.m. in the Portuguese capital.  Camargo Correa, through its Intercement Austria subsidiary,
bid 5.50 euros a share for Lisbon-based Cimpor, Intercement said
in a filing with the Portuguese securities regulator after the
market closed on March 30.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joao Lima at 
 jlima1@bloomberg.net  